#8004
Cave Deep Inside a Mountain~
The rough stone walls depict several layers of stratified stone that must
have lain unseen for milennia before this tunnel ever opened to the outer
world.  Now, following eons of slow errosion the bands of color are
begining to wear away forming slight shelves where sturdier rock has
eroded slower than the softer stone.  Fortunately the slow errosion,
though it has millenia to go before making any real progress yet, has
already widened the tunnel enough to keep it passable.  The tunnel seems
to widen as it moves north, yet it tightens into narrow confines as it
twists eastward.
~
