#8006
A Large Hall Cut into the Stone~
Soaring up several feet on both sides of you are smooth, stone walls cut
straight from the mountains.  Hanging from each wall are heavy cloth
tapestries depicting a legion of white-robed dwarves walking about a
large temple.  The floor has been cut from grey marble which streaks of
black running through it.  Set in the center of the chamber is a large
stone fountain adorned with carefully-detailed carvings of dwarven
rituals.  Set into the southern wall is a large iron door covered in
decades of dust and grime.  To the north, east, and west tunnels cut
their way deeper into the heart of the underground complex.
